obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3638)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3638&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Semiconductor`
  line `Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Act, 2000.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st May, 2004 (Ss. 3 and 5), vide notification No. S.O. 278(E), dated 12th February, 2004, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `15th January, 2014 (Ss. 93 and 94), vide notification No. S.O. 84(E), dated 10th January, 2014, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3639)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3639&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unles the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Appellate Board" means the Appellate Board established under section 32;`
  line
  line `(b) "assignment" means an assignment in writing by act of the parties concerned;`
  line
  line `(c) "Bench" means a Bench of the Appellate Board;`
  line
  line `(d) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Appellate Board;`
  line
  line `(e) "commercial exploitation", in relation to Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design,`
  line `means to sell, lease, offer or exhibit for sale or otherwise distribute such semiconductor integrated`
  line `circuit for any commercial purpose;`
  line
  line `(f) "convention country" means a country notified as such under section 93;`
  line
  line `(g) "Judicial Member" means a Member of the Appellate Board appointed as such under this Act,`
  line `and includes the Chairperson or such Vice-Chairperson who possesses any of the qualifications`
  line `specified in sub-section (3) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(h) "layout-design" means a layout of transistors and other circuitry elements and includes lead`
  line `wires connecting such elements and expressed in any manner in a semiconductor integrated circuit;`
  line
  line `(i) "Member" means a Judicial Member or a Technical Member of the Appellate Board and`
  line `includes the Chairperson and the Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(j) "notify" means to notify in the Semiconductor Integrated Circuit Journal published by the`
  line Registrar;
  line
  line `(k) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "register" means the Register of Layout-Designs referred to in section 6;`
  line
  line `(m) "registered" (with its grammatical variations) means registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "registered layout-design" means a layout-design which is actually on the register;`
  line
  line `(o) "registered proprietor", in relation to a layout-design, means the person for the time being`
  line `entered in the register as proprietor of the layout-design;`
  line
  line `(p) "registered user" means a person who is for the time being registered as such under section`
  line 25;
  line
  line `(q) "Registrar" means the Registrar of Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design referred`
  line `to in section 3;`
  line
  line `(r) "semiconductor integrated circuit" means a product having transistors and other circuitry`
  line `elements which are inseparably formed on a semiconductor material or an insulating material or`
  line `inside the semiconductor material and designed to perform an electronic circuitry function;`
  line
  line `(s) "Technical Member" means a Member of the Appellate Board who is not a Judicial Member`
  line `and includes the Chairperson or such Vice-Chairperson who possesses any of the qualifications`
  line `specified in sub-section (4) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(t) "transmission" means transmission by operation of law, devolution on the personal`
  line `representation of a deceased person or any other mode of transfer not being assignment;`
  line
  line `(u) "Vice-Chairperson" means the Vice-Chairperson of the Appellate Board;`
  line
  line `(v) any reference to the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry shall be`
  line `construed as including a reference to any office of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits LayoutDesign`
  line Registry.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3640)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Registrar of Semiconductor Integrated Circuits layout-design.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3640&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint a person to be known as the Registrar of`
  line `Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such other officers with such designation as it thinks fit for`
  line `the purpose of discharging, under the superintendence and direction of the Registrar, such functions of the`
  line `Registrar under this Act as he may from time to time authorise them to discharge.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3641)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power of Registrar to transfer pending matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3641&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the generality of the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) of section 3, the Registrar may, by order in writing and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded therein, withdraw any matter pending before an officer appointed under the said sub-section (2)`
  line `and deal with such matter himself either de novo or from the stage it was so withdrawn or transferred the same to another officer so appointed who may subject to the special direction in the order of transfer deal`
  line `with the matter either de novo or from the stage it was so transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3642)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Registry.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3642&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, there shall be established a Registry which shall be`
  line `known as the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry shall be at such`
  line `place as the Central Government may specify and for the purposes of facilitating the registration of`
  line `layout-designs, there may be established, at such places as the Central Government may think fit, branch`
  line `offices of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, define the territorial limits`
  line `within which an office of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry may exercise its`
  line functions.
  line
  line `(4) There shall be seal of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3643)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Register of Layout-Designs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3643&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, a record called the Register of`
  line `Layout-Designs shall be kept at the head office of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design`
  line `Registry wherein shall be entered all registered layout-designs with the names, addresses and descriptions`
  line `of the proprietor and such other matters related to the registered layout-designs as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the superintendence and direction of the Central Government, the register shall be kept`
  line `under the control and management of the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be kept at each Branch office of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design`
  line `Registry a copy of the register and other documents as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3644)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Prohibition of registration of certain layout-designs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3644&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) A layout-design--`
  line
  line `(a) which is not original; or`
  line
  line `(b) which has been commercially exploited anywhere in India or in a convention country; or`
  line
  line `(c) which is not inherently distinctive; or`
  line
  line `(d) which is not inherently capable of being distinguishable from any other registered layoutdesign,`
  line
  line `shall not be registered as a layout-design:`
  line
  line `Provided that a layout-design which has been commercially exploited for not more than two years`
  line `from the date on which an application for its registration has been filed either in India or in a convention`
  line `country shall be treated as not having been commercially exploited for the purposes of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) A layout-design shall be considered to be original if it is the result of its creator's own intellectual`
  line `efforts and is not commonly known to the creators of layout-designs and manufacturers of semiconductor`
  line `integrated circuits at the time of its creation:`
  line
  line `Provided that a layout-design consisting of such combination of elements and interconnections that`
  line `are commonly known among creators of layout-designs and manufacturers of semiconductor integrated`
  line `circuits shall be considered as original if such combination taken as a whole is the result of its creator's`
  line `own intellectual efforts.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an original layout-design has been created in execution of a commission or a contract of`
  line `employment, the right of registration to such layout-design under this Act shall belong, in the absence of`
  line `any contractual provision to the contrary, to the person who commissioned the work or to the employer.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3645)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Application for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3645&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person claiming to be the creator of a layout-design, who`
  line `is desirous of registering it, shall apply in writing to the Registrar in the prescribed manner for the`
  line `registration of his layout-design.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be filed in the office of the Semiconductor Integrated`
  line `Circuits Layout-Design Registry within whose territorial limits the principal place of business in India of`
  line `the applicant or in the case of joint application the principal place of business in India of the applicant`
  line `whose name is first mentioned in the application, as having a place of business in India, is situate:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the applicant or any of the joint applicant does not carry on business in India, the`
  line `application shall be filed in the office of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry`
  line `within whose territorial limits the place mentioned in the address for service in India as disclosed in the`
  line `application is situate.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Registrar may refuse the application or may accept it`
  line `absolutely or subject to such amendments or modifications, as he may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3646)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Withdrawal of acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3646&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Where after the acceptance of an application for registration of`
  line `layout-design, but before its registration, the Registrar is satisfied that the layout-design is prohibited of`
  line `registration under section 7, the Registrar may, after hearing the applicant if he so desires, withdraw the`
  line `acceptance and proceed as if the application had not been accepted.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3647)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Advertisement of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3647&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an application for registration of a layout-design has`
  line `been accepted, the Registrar shall, within fourteen days after the date of acceptance, cause the application`
  line `as accepted to be advertised in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(2) Where after advertisement of an application--`
  line
  line `(a) an error in the application has been corrected; or`
  line
  line `(b) the application has been permitted to be amended under section 12,`
  line
  line `the Registrar may in his discretion cause the application to be advertised again or, in any case falling`
  line `under clause (b), may, instead of causing the application to be advertised again, notify in the prescribed`
  line `manner the correction or amendment made in the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3648)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Opposition to registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3648&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person may, within three months from the date of the`
  line `advertisement or re-advertisement of an application for registration or within such further period, not`
  line `exceeding one month in the aggregate, as the Registrar, on application made to him in the prescribed`
  line `manner and on payment of the prescribed fee, allows, give notice in writing in the prescribed manner to`
  line `the Registrar of opposition to the registration.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall serve a copy of the notice on the applicant for registration and, within two`
  line `months from the receipt by the applicant of such copy of the notice of opposition, the applicant shall send`
  line `to the Registrar in the prescribed manner a counter-statement of the grounds on which he relies for his`
  line `application and if he does not do so, he shall be deemed to have abandoned his application.`
  line
  line `(3) If the applicant sends such counter-statement, the Registrar shall serve a copy thereof on the`
  line `person giving notice of opposition.`
  line
  line `(4) Any evidence upon which the opponent and the applicant may rely shall be submitted in the`
  line `prescribed manner and within the prescribed time to the Registrar, the Registrar shall give an opportunity`
  line `to them to be heard, if they so desire.`
  line
  line `(5) The Registrar shall, after hearing the parties, if so required, and considering the evidence, decide,`
  line `after taking into account any ground of objection whether relied upon by the opponent or not.`
  line
  line `(6) When a person giving notice of opposition or an applicant sending a counter-statement after`
  line `receipt of a copy of such notice neither resides nor carries on business in India, the Registrar may require`
  line `him to give security for the costs of proceedings before him and, in default of such security being duly`
  line `given, may treat the opposition or application, as the case may be, as abandoned.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3649)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Correction and amendment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3649&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may on such terms as he thinks just--`
  line
  line `(a) at any time, whether before or after acceptance of an application for registration under section`
  line `8, permit the correction of any error in or in connection with the application or permit an amendment`
  line `of the application; or`
  line
  line `(b) permit correction of any error in, or an amendment of, a notice of opposition or a counterstatement`
  line `under section 11.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3650)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3650&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 9, when an application for the registration`
  line `of the layout-design has been accepted and either--`
  line
  line `(a) the application has not been opposed and time for notice of opposition has expired; or`
  line
  line `(b) the application has been opposed and the opposition has been decided in favour of the`
  line applicant,
  line
  line `the Registrar shall register the said layout-design in the register and the layout-design shall be registered`
  line `as of the date of the making of the said application and that date shall be deemed to be the date of`
  line registration.
  line
  line `(2) On the registration of a layout-design, the Registrar shall issue to the applicant a certificate in the`
  line `prescribed form of the registration thereof sealed with the seal of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits`
  line `Layout-Design Registry.`
  line
  line `(3) Where registration of a layout-design is not completed within twelve months from the date of the`
  line `application by reason of default on the part of the applicant, the Registrar may, after giving notice to the`
  line `applicant in the prescribed manner, treat the application as abandoned unless it is completed within the`
  line `time specified in that behalf in the notice.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar may amend the register or a certificate of registration for the purpose of correcting a`
  line `clerical error or an obvious mistake.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3651)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Jointly owned layout-design.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3651&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided in sub-section (2), nothing in this Act shall`
  line `authorise the registration of two or more persons who claim to be the creator of a layout-design.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the relation between two or more persons claiming to be the creator of layout-design are`
  line `such that--`
  line
  line `(a) both of them or all of them have put the combined intellectual effort in creating such design;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the creation of such layout-design both of them or all of them are connected in`
  line `such manner that intellectual effort of each of them are not distinguishable in creation of such layout design,`
  line
  line `those persons may be registered as joint proprietor of the layout-design and this Act shall have effect in`
  line `relation to any right to the use of the layout-design vested in those persons as if in those rights vested in a`
  line `single person.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3652)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Duration of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3652&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The registration of a layout-design shall be only for a period of ten`
  line `years counted from the date of filing an application for registration or from the date of first commercial`
  line `exploitation anywhere in India or in any country whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3653)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `No action of infringement of unregistered layout-design.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3653&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be entitled to`
  line `institute any proceeding to prevent, or to recover damages for, the infringement of an unregistered layout design.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3654)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Rights conferred by registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3654&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the registration of`
  line `a layout-design shall, if valid, give to the registered proprietor of layout-design the exclusive right to the`
  line `use of the layout-design and to obtain relief in respect of infringement in the manner provided by this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the rights conferred by the`
  line `registration of a layout-design shall be available to the registered proprietor of that layout-design`
  line `irrespective of the fact as to whether the layout-design is incorporated in an article or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (3655)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Infringement of layout-design.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3655&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered layout-design is infringed by a person who,`
  line `not being the registered proprietor of the layout-design or a registered user thereof,--`
  line
  line `(a) does any act of reproducing, whether by incorporating in a semiconductor integrated circuit or`
  line `otherwise, a registered layout-design in its entirety or any part thereof, except such act of reproducing`
  line `any part thereof which is not original within the meaning sub-section (2) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the provisions of sub-section (5), does any act of importing or selling or otherwise`
  line `distributing for commercial purposes a registered layout-design or a semiconductor integrated circuit`
  line `incorporating such registered layout-design or an article incorporating such a semiconductor`
  line `integrated circuit containing such registered layout-design for the use of which such person is not`
  line `entitled under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 17, sub-section (1) or sub-section (5), the`
  line `performance of the act of reproduction referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1), where such act is`
  line `performed for the limited purposes of scientific evaluation, analysis, research or teaching, shall not`
  line `constitute act of infringement within the meaning of that clause.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person, on the basis of scientific evaluation or analysis of a registered layout-design,`
  line `creates another layout-design which is original within the meaning of sub-section (2) of section 7, that`
  line `person shall have the right to incorporate such another layout-design in a semiconductor integrated circuit`
  line `or to perform any of the acts referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (5) in respect of such another`
  line `layout-design and such incorporation or performance of any act shall not be regarded as infringement`
  line `within the meaning of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Where a layout-design is created by the process of scientific evaluation or analysis of the`
  line `registered layout-design as referred to in sub-section (3), the use of such layout-design by the proprietor`
  line `of such registered layout-design shall be regarded as infringement within the meaning of sub-section (1)`
  line `after the date of registration of such layout-design under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (b) of sub-section (1), the performance of any of the`
  line `acts referred to in that clause by a person shall not be regarded as infringement within the meaning of that`
  line `clause if such act is performed or directed to be performed in respect of a semiconductor integrated circuit`
  line `incorporating a registered layout-design or any article incorporating such a semiconductor integrated`
  line `circuit where such person does not possess any knowledge or has no reasonable ground to know while performing or directing to be performed such act in respect of such semiconductor integrated circuit or`
  line `article that it incorporated a registered layout-design but after the time when such person has received`
  line `notice of such knowledge, he may continue to perform or directing to be performed such act in respect of`
  line `the stock on hand or ordered before such time and, then, he shall be liable to pay the proprietor of the`
  line `registered layout-design a sum by way of royalty to be determined by negotiation between registered`
  line `proprietor of the registered layout-design and that person or by the Appellate Board having regard to the`
  line `benefit accrued to such person by performing or directing to be performed such act in respect of such`
  line `semiconductor integrated circuit or article, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any other person purchases a semiconductor integrated circuit incorporating a registered`
  line `layout-design or any article incorporating such a semiconductor integrated circuit referred to in`
  line `sub-section (5) from a person referred to in that sub-section, then, such other person shall be entitled to`
  line `the immunity from infringement in respect of that semiconductor integrated circuit or article, as the case`
  line `may be, to the extent and in the manner as if the word person referred in that sub-section includes the`
  line `word any other person referred in this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing contained in clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall be construed as constituting an act of`
  line `infringement where any person performs any of the acts specified in that clause with the written consent`
  line `of the registered proprietor of a registered layout-design or within the control of the person obtaining such`
  line `consent, or in respect of a registered layout-design or a semiconductor integrated circuit incorporating a`
  line `registered layout-design or any article incorporating such a semiconductor integrated circuit, that has been`
  line `put on the market by or with the consent of the registered proprietor of such registered layout-design.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where any person by application of independent`
  line `intellect has created a layout-design which is identical to a registered layout-design, then, any act of such`
  line `person in respect of the layout-design so created shall not be the infringement of the registered layoutdesign.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (3656)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Registration to be prima facie evidence of validity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3656&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all legal proceedings relating to a`
  line `layout-design registered under this Act (including application under section 30), the original registration`
  line `of the layout-design and all subsequent assignments and transmissions of layout-design shall be prima`
  line `facie evidence of the validity thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In all legal proceedings as aforesaid, a registered layout-design shall not be held to be invalid on`
  line `the ground that it was not a registerable layout-design under section 7 except upon evidence of originality`
  line `and that such evidence was not submitted to the Registrar before registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (3657)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of Registered Proprietor to assign and give receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3657&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The person for the time being`
  line `included in the register as proprietor of a layout-design shall, subject to the provisions of this Act and to`
  line `any right appearing from the register to be vested in any other person, have power to assign the layoutdesign,`
  line `and to give effectual receipts for any consideration for such assignment.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (3658)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Assignability and transmissibility of registered layout-design.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3658&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in`
  line `any other law to the contrary, a registered layout-design shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, be`
  line `assignable and transmissible whether with or without the goodwill of the business concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (3659)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Conditions for assignment otherwise than in connection with the goodwill of a business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3659&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where an assignment of a registered layout-design is made otherwise than in connection with the`
  line `goodwill of business in which such layout-design has been or is used, the assignment shall not take effect unless the assignee, not later than the expiration of six months from the date on which the assignment is`
  line `made or within such extended period, if any, not exceeding three months in the aggregate, as the Registrar`
  line `may allow, apply to the Registrar for directions with respect to the advertisement of the assignment, and`
  line `advertises it in such form and manner and within such period as the Registrar may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (3660)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Registration of assignments and transmissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3660&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person becomes entitled by`
  line `assignment or transmission to a registered layout-design, he shall apply in the prescribed manner to the`
  line `Registrar to register his title, and the Registrar shall, on receipt of the application and on proof of his title`
  line `to his satisfaction, register him as the proprietor of the layout-design and shall cause particulars of the`
  line `assignment or transmission to be entered on the register:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the validity of an assignment of transmission is in dispute between the parties,`
  line `the Registrar may refuse to register the assignment or transmission until the rights of the party have been`
  line `determined by a competent court.`
  line
  line `(2) Except for the purpose of an application before the Registrar under sub-section (1) or an appeal`
  line `from an order thereon, or an application under section 30 or an appeal from an order thereon, a document`
  line `or instrument in respect of which no entry has been made in the register in accordance with sub-section`
  line `(1), shall not be admitted in evidence by the Registrar or the Appellate Board or any court in proof of title`
  line `to the layout-design by assignment or transmission unless the Registrar or the Appellate Board or the`
  line `court, as the case may be, otherwise directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (3661)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Registered users.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3661&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 25, a person other than the registered`
  line `proprietor of a layout-design may be registered as a registered user thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (3662)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Registration as registered user.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3662&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it is proposed that a person should be registered as`
  line `a registered user of a layout-design, the registered proprietor and the proposed registered user shall jointly`
  line `apply in writing to the Registrar in the prescribed manner and every such application shall be`
  line `accompanied by--`
  line
  line `(a) the agreement in writing or a duly authenticated copy thereof, entered into between the`
  line `registered proprietor and the proposed registered user with respect to the permitted use of the layout-design;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) an affidavit made by the registered proprietor or by some person authorised to the satisfaction`
  line `of Registrar to act on his behalf--`
  line
  line `(i) giving particulars of the relationship, existing or proposed, between the registered`
  line `proprietor and the proposed registered user, including particulars showing the degree of control`
  line `by the proprietor over the permitted use which the relationship will confer and whether it is a`
  line `term of their relationship that the proposed registered user shall be sole registered user or that`
  line `there shall be any other restriction as to persons for whose registration as registered user`
  line `application may be made;`
  line
  line `(ii) stating the conditions or restrictions, if any, proposed with respect to the place of`
  line `permitted use or any other matter;`
  line
  line `(iii) stating whether the permitted use to be for a period or without limit of period, and, if for`
  line `a period, the duration thereof; and`
  line
  line `(c) such further documents or other evidence as may be required by the Registrar or as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) Where the requirement of sub-section (1) have been complied with, the Registrar shall register the`
  line `proposed registered user.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall issue notice in the prescribed manner of the registration of a person as a`
  line `registered user to other registered users of the layout-design, if any.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall, if so requested by the applicant, take steps of securing that information given`
  line `for the purposes of an application under this section (other than matters entered in the register) is not`
  line `disclosed to rivals in trade.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (3663)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of Registrar for cancellation of registration as registered user.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3663&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice`
  line `to the provisions of section 30, the registration of a person as registered user--`
  line
  line `(a) may be cancelled by the Registrar on application in writing in the prescribed manner of the`
  line `registered proprietor or of the registered user or of any other registered user of the layout-design;`
  line
  line `(b) may be cancelled by the Registrar on the application in writing in the prescribed manner of`
  line `any person on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the registered user has used the layout-design otherwise than in accordance with the`
  line `agreement under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the proprietor or the registered user misrepresented, or failed to disclose, some fact`
  line `material to the application for registration which if accurately represented or disclosed would not`
  line `have justified the registration of the registered user;`
  line
  line `(iii) that the circumstances have changed since the date of registration in such a way that at`
  line `the date of such application for cancellation they would not have justified registration of the`
  line `registered user;`
  line
  line `(iv) that the registration ought not to have been effected having regard to right vested in the`
  line `applicant by virtue of a contract in the performance of which he is interested;`
  line
  line `(c) may be cancelled by the Registrar on his own motion or on the application in writing in the`
  line `prescribed manner by any person on the ground that any stipulation in the agreement between the`
  line `registered proprietor and the registered user regarding the topographical dimensions of the layout design`
  line `is either not being enforced or is not being complied with;`
  line
  line `(d) may be cancelled by the Registrar if the layout-design is no longer registered.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall issue notice in the prescribed manner in respect of every application under this`
  line `section to the registered proprietor and each registered user (not being the applicant) of the layout-design.`
  line
  line `(3) The procedure for cancelling a registration shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before cancelling of registration, the registered proprietor shall be given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (3664)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power of Registrar to call for information relating to agreement in respect of registered users.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3664&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may, at any time during the continuance of the registration of the registered`
  line `user, by notice in writing, require the registered proprietor to confirm to him within one month that the`
  line `agreement filed under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 25 continues to be in force.`
  line
  line `(2) If the registered proprietor fails to furnish the confirmation within one month as required under`
  line `sub-section (1), the registered user shall cease to be the registered user on the day immediately after the`
  line `expiry of said period and the Registrar shall notify the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (3665)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Right of registered user to take proceedings against infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3665&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any agreement`
  line `subsisting between the parties, a registered user may make complaint before the competent criminal court`
  line `for the infringement in his own name as if he were the registered proprietor.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (3666)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Registered user not to have right of assignment or transmission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3666&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall`
  line `confer on a registered user of a layout-design any assignable or transmissible right to the use thereof.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--The right of a registered user of a layout-design shall not deem to have been`
  line `assigned or transmitted within the meaning of this section in the following cases, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the registered user being an individual enters into a partnership with any other person`
  line `for carrying on the business concerned; but in any such case the firm may use the layout-design, if`
  line `otherwise in force, only for so long as the registered user is a member of the firm;`
  line
  line `(b) where the registered user being a firm subsequently undergoes a change in its constitution; but`
  line `in any such case the reconstituted firm may use the layout-design, if otherwise in force, only for so`
  line `long as any partner of the original firm at the time of its registration as registered user, continues to be`
  line `a partner of the reconstituted firm.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of Explanation I, "firm" has the same meaning as in the Indian`
  line `Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (3667)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to rectify the register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3667&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by the absence or omission from the`
  line `register of any entry, or by any entry made in the register without sufficient cause, or by any entry`
  line `wrongly remaining on the register, or by any error or defect in any entry in the register, may apply in the`
  line `prescribed manner to the Appellate Board or to the Registrar, and the Appellate Board or the Registrar, as`
  line `the case may be, may make such order for making, expunging or varying the entry as it may think it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Board or the Registrar may in any proceedings under this section decide any`
  line `question that may be necessary or expedient to decide in connection with the rectification of the register.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appellate Board or the Registrar, of its own motion, may, after giving notice in the prescribed`
  line `manner to the parties concerned and after giving them an opportunity of being heard, make any order`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Any order of the Appellate Board rectifying the register shall direct that notice of the rectification`
  line `shall be served upon the Registrar in the prescribed manner who shall upon receipt of such notice, rectify`
  line `the register accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (3668)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Correction of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3668&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may, on application made in the prescribed manner by`
  line `the registered proprietor,--`
  line
  line `(a) correct any error in the name, address or description of the registered proprietor of a layoutdesign,`
  line `or any other entry relating to the layout-design;`
  line
  line `(b) enter any change in the name, address or description of the person who is registered as`
  line `proprietor of a layout-design;`
  line
  line `(c) cancel the entry of a layout-design on the register,`
  line
  line `and may make any consequential amendment or alteration in the certificate of registration, and for that`
  line `purpose, may require the certificate of registration to be produced to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may, on application made in the prescribed manner by a registered user of a layoutdesign,`
  line `and after notice to the registered proprietor, correct any error, or enter any change in the name,`
  line `address or description of the registered user.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (3669)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Establishment of Layout-Design Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3669&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, establish an Appellate Board to be known as the Layout-Design`
  line `Appellate Board to exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on it by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (3670)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Composition of Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3670&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Board shall consist of a Chairperson,`
  line `Vice-Chairperson, and such other Members as the Central Government may deem fit and, subject to the`
  line `other provisions of this Act, the jurisdiction, powers and authority of the Appellate Board may be`
  line `exercised by a Bench thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, a Bench shall consist of one Judicial Member and one`
  line `Technical Member and shall sit at such place as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Chairperson--`
  line
  line `(a) may, in addition to discharging the functions of the Judicial Member or Technical Member of`
  line `the Bench to which he is appointed, discharge the function of the Judicial Member or, as the case may`
  line `be, the Technical Member, of any other Bench;`
  line
  line `(b) may transfer a Member from one Bench to another Bench;`
  line
  line `(c) may authorise Vice-Chairperson, the Judicial Member or the Technical Member appointed to`
  line `one Bench to discharge also the functions of the Judicial Member or the Technical Member, as the`
  line `case may be, of another Bench.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any Benches are constituted, the Central Government may, from time to time, by`
  line `notification, make provisions as to the distribution of the business of the Appellate Board amongst the`
  line `Benches and specify the matters which may be dealt by each Bench.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the expression "matter" includes`
  line `an application or appeal under section 40 or section 42.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point, they shall state the point or points on`
  line `which they differ, and make a reference to the Chairperson who shall either hear the point or points`
  line `himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or points by one or more of the other Members and`
  line `such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Members who have`
  line `heard the case including those who first heard it.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (3671)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Qualifications for appointment as Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson, or other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3671&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1)A person shall not be qualified for appointment as Chairperson unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) has, for at least two years, held the office of a Vice-Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Vice-Chairperson, unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) has, for at least two years, held the office of a Judicial Member or a Technical Member; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been a member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a post in Grade I of that Service`
  line `or any higher post for at least five years.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Judicial Member unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been a member of the Indian Legal Service and has held the post in Grade I of that Service`
  line `for at least three years; or`
  line
  line `(b) has, for at least ten years, held a civil judicial office.`
  line
  line `(4) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Technical Member, unless he possesses a`
  line `Master's Degree in Physics or Bachelor's Degree in Electronics Engineering or Electrical Engineering or`
  line `Computer Engineering from an University or Institution established under law for the time being in force`
  line `and has held a post equivalent to the post of Joint Secretary to the Government of India or any higher post`
  line `for at least five years and possesses at least five years' experience in the area of semiconductors.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (6), the Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and every other`
  line `Member shall be appointed by the President of India.`
  line
  line `(6) No appointment of a person as the Chairperson shall be made except after consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (3672)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Term of office of Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3672&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, ViceChairperson`
  line `or other Member shall hold office as such for a term of five years from the date on which he`
  line `enters upon his office or until he attains,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of Chairperson and Vice-Chairperson, the age of sixty-five years; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of Member, the age of sixty-two years, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (3673)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Vice-Chairperson or senior-most Member to act as Chairperson or discharge his function in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3673&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson`
  line `by reason of his death, resignation or otherwise, the Vice-Chairperson and in his absence the senior-most`
  line `Member shall act as Chairperson until the date on which a new Chairperson, appointed in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy, enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairperson in unable to discharge his functions owing to his absence, illness or any`
  line `other cause, the Vice-Chairperson and in his absence the senior-most Member shall discharge the`
  line `functions of the Chairperson until the date on which the Chairperson resumes his duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (3674)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Salaries, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3674&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The salaries and allowance payable to, and other terms and`
  line `conditions of service (including pension, gratuity and other retirement benefits) of, the Chairperson,`
  line `Vice-Chairperson and other Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a person who, immediately before the date`
  line `of assuming office as the Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson or other Member, was in service of Government`
  line `shall be deemed to have retired from service on the date on which he enters upon as the Chairperson,`
  line `Vice-Chairperson or other Member, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (3675)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3675&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and any other Member may,`
  line `by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the President of India, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson or any other Member shall, unless he is permitted by`
  line `the President of India to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters`
  line `upon his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson or any other Member shall not be removed from his office`
  line `except by an order by the President of India on the ground of proved misbehaviour or incapacity after an`
  line `enquiry made by a Judge of the Supreme Court in which the Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson or other`
  line `Member has been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard`
  line `in respect of those charges.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by rules, regulate the procedure for the investigation of`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity of the Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson or other Member referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (3676)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Staff of Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3676&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall determine the nature and`
  line `categories of the officers and other employees required to assist the Appellate Board in the discharge of`
  line `its functions and provide the Appellate Board with such officers and other employees as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and other allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other employees of`
  line `the Appellate Board shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The officers and other employees of the Appellate Board shall discharge their functions under the`
  line `general superintendence of the Chairperson in the manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (3677)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Application to the Appellate Board to determine royalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3677&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registered proprietor of a`
  line `registered layout-design may make an application to the Appellate Board for determination of royalty`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 18.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and be accompanied by such`
  line `affidavits, documents or any other evidence and by such fee in respect of the filing of such application`
  line `and by such other fees for the service or execution of processes as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Appellate Board shall, after giving notice to`
  line `the opposite party to file opposition within the prescribed time and manner and after giving opportunity of`
  line `being heard to the applicant and the opposite party, dispose of the application.`
  line
  line `(4) An order or decision made by the Appellate Board in disposing of the application under subsection`
  line `(3) shall be executable by a civil court having local jurisdiction as if it were a decree made by that`
  line court.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (3678)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of the Board to cancel registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3678&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person may make an application, in the`
  line `prescribed form accompanied by prescribed fee, to the Appellate Board for cancellation of the registration`
  line `of a layout-design registered under this Act or registration of assignment or transmission relating thereto,`
  line `as the case may be, on the ground that--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the registration of a layout-design, the layout-design is prohibited for being`
  line `registered under section 7; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of the registration of assignment or transmission relating to a registered layoutdesign,`
  line `such assignment or transmission is contrary to any provision of the law for the time being in`
  line force.
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Board shall, on receipt of an application under sub-section (1), give notice to the`
  line `opposite parties in the prescribed manner and after giving them an opportunity of being heard, make such`
  line `order as it may deem fit regarding cancellation of registration:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the ground of cancellation has been established with respect only to a part of a`
  line `layout-design, the Board shall cancel only such part and the remaining part of the layout-design if capable`
  line `of performing as a semiconductor integrated circuit shall be retained as registered on the register in the`
  line `name of the registered proprietor of such layout-design.`
  line
  line `(3) Any cancellation of the registration of a layout-design either in whole or in part under sub-section`
  line `(2) shall be deemed to be effective on the date from which the period of ten years referred to in section 15`
  line `is countable in respect of that layout-design.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Board shall, without delay after making any order of cancellation under sub-section`
  line `(2), send a copy of such order to the Registrar who shall correct the register to give effect to such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (3679)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Appeal to Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3679&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order or decision of the Registrar`
  line `under this Act, or the rules made thereunder may prefer an appeal to the Appellate Board within three`
  line `months from the date on which the order or decision sought to be appealed against is communicated to`
  line `such person preferring the appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of the period specified under subsection`
  line `(1):`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period specified therefor, if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the Appellate Board that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the`
  line `specified period.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal to the Appellate Board shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and shall be accompanied by a copy of the order or decision appealed against and by`
  line `such fees as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (3680)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Procedure and powers of Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3680&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Board shall not be bound by the`
  line `procedure laid down in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) but shall be guided by principles of`
  line `natural justice and, subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the Appellate`
  line `Board shall have powers to regulate its own procedure including the fixing of places and times of its`
  line hearing.
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Board shall have, for the purpose of discharging its functions under this Act, the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while`
  line `trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) receiving evidence;`
  line
  line `(b) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(c) requisitioning any public record; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any proceeding before the Appellate Board shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purpose of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860), and the Appellate Board shall be deemed to be a civil court for all the purposes of section 195 and`
  line `Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (3681)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of courts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3681&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `No court or other authority shall have or, be entitled to,`
  line `exercise any jurisdiction, powers or authority in relation to the matters referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 40 or sub-section (1) of section 42.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (3682)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Bar to appear before Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3682&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `On ceasing to hold office, the Chairperson, ViceChairperson`
  line `or other Members shall not appear before the Appellate Board or the Registrar.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (3683)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Conditions as to making of interim order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3683&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `provisions of this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, no interim order (whether by way of`
  line `injunction or stay or any other manner) shall be made on, or in any proceedings relating to, an appeal`
  line unless--
  line
  line `(a) copies of such appeal and of all documents in support of the plea for such interim order are`
  line `furnished to the party against whom such appeal is made or proposed to be made; and`
  line
  line `(b) opportunity is given to such party to be heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (3684)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power of Chairperson to transfer cases from one Bench to another.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3684&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `On the application of`
  line `any of the parties and after notice to the parties, and after hearing such of them as he may desire to be`
  line `heard, or on his own motion without such notice, the Chairperson may transfer any case pending before`
  line `one Bench, for disposal, to any other Bench.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (3685)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Procedure for application for rectification, etc., before Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3685&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application`
  line `for rectification of the register made to the Appellate Board under section 30 shall be in such form as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A certified copy of every order or judgment of the Appellate Board relating to a registered layoutdesign`
  line `under this Act shall be communicated to the Registrar by the Board and the Registrar shall give`
  line `effect to the order of the Board and shall, when so directed, amend the entries in, or rectify, the register in`
  line `accordance with such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (3686)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Appearance of Registrar in legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3686&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar shall have the right to appear`
  line `and be heard--`
  line
  line `(a) in any legal proceedings before the Appellate Board in which the relief sought includes`
  line `alteration or rectification of the register or in which any question relating to the practice of the`
  line `Semiconductor Integrated Circuit Layout-Design Registry is raised;`
  line
  line `(b) in any appeal to the Board from an order of the Registrar on an application for registration of`
  line `a layout-design--`
  line
  line `(i) which is not opposed, and the application is either refused by the Registrar or is accepted`
  line `by him subject to any amendments or modifications, or`
  line
  line `(ii) which has been opposed and the Registrar considers that his appearance is necessary in`
  line `the public interest,`
  line
  line `and the Registrar shall appear in any case if so directed by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless the Appellate Board otherwise directs, the Registrar may, in lieu of appearing, submit a`
  line `statement in writing signed by him, giving such particulars as he thinks proper of the proceedings before`
  line `him relating to the matter in issue or of the grounds of any decision given by him affecting it, or of the`
  line `practice of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry in like cases, or of other`
  line `matters relevant to the issues and within his knowledge as Registrar, and such statement shall be evidence`
  line `in the proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (3687)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Registrar to refer certain disputes to the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3687&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `If any question arises in any proceedings`
  line `before Registrar, whether a layout-design has been commercially exploited for more than two years`
  line `anywhere in a convention country for the purpose of registration of such layout-design under this Act, the`
  line `Registrar shall refer such question to the Appellate Board, and the decision of the Board thereon shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (3688)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power of the Board to permit certain uses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3688&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act, the Appellate Board may on an application made in the prescribed manner before it on behalf of the`
  line `Government or by any person authorised by the Government and after giving notice of such application to`
  line `the registered proprietor of a layout-design and providing the opportunity of being heard to the parties`
  line `concerned permit the use of such registered layout-design by the Government or by such person so`
  line `authorised, as the case may be, subject to any or all of the following conditions as the Board deems fit`
  line `under the circumstances of such use, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the use of the layout-design shall be for non-commercial public purposes or for the`
  line `purposes relating to national emergency or of extreme public urgency;`
  line
  line `(b) that the duration of the use of the layout-design shall be limited for a period specified by the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(c) that the use of the layout-design shall be non-assignable and non-transmissible;`
  line
  line `(d) that the use of the layout-design shall be to the extent which the Board deems necessary to`
  line `remedy the anti-competitive practice;`
  line
  line `(e) that the use of the layout-design shall be predominantly for the supply of semiconductor`
  line `integrated circuits or articles incorporating semiconductor integrated circuits in domestic market of`
  line `India:`
  line
  line `Provided that Board shall not permit the use of a registered layout-design, by any such person`
  line `authorised by the Government, under this sub-section unless the Board is satisfied that such person so`
  line `authorised has made efforts to enter into agreement with the registered proprietor of such layout-design`
  line `on reasonable commercial terms and conditions for permitted use of such layout-design and such efforts`
  line `had not been successful within prescribed period:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the first proviso shall not be applicable in a case where the person so authorised`
  line `produces to the Board a certificate issued by the Government to the effect that such use is required due to`
  line `national emergency or any other circumstances which the Government considers to be of extreme urgency`
  line `or of public non-commercial use.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Board shall, while granting the permission for the use of a registered layout-design`
  line `under sub-section (1), determine the amount of royalty to be paid by the Government or the person`
  line `authorised by the Government, as the case may be, to the registered proprietor of such layout-design for`
  line `such permitted use.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appellate Board may, on the application of the registered proprietor of a layout-design`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1), may review the permission granted under that sub-section and, after giving`
  line `notice and opportunity of hearing to the parties concerned in the prescribed manner, cancel or amend such`
  line `permission if the Board is satisfied that any of the conditions subject to which the permission was granted`
  line `has not been observed or the circumstances which led to the granting of such permission has ceased to`
  line `exist or substantially altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (3689)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Costs of Registrar in proceedings before Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3689&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `In all proceedings under this Act`
  line `before the Appellate Board the costs of the Registrar shall be in the discretion of the Board, but the`
  line `Registrar shall not be ordered to pay the costs of any of the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (3690)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3690&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Appellate Board under this`
  line `Act may, within the prescribed period appeal to the High Court within whose the jurisdiction of head`
  line `office or the branch office of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry against the`
  line `decision or order of which the appeal arises is situated.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such appeal shall be preferred by petition in writing and shall be in such form and shall`
  line `contain such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the provisions of the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) shall apply to appeals before a High Court under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (3691)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Powers of High Courts to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3691&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may make rules consistent with this`
  line `Act as to the conduct and procedure of all proceeding under this Act before it.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (3692)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3692&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, till the establishment`
  line `of the Appellate Board under section 32, the Intellectual Property Appellate Board establishment under`
  line `section 83 of the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of 1999) shall exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority`
  line `conferred on the Appellate Board under this Act subject to the modification that in any Bench of such`
  line `Intellectual Property Appellate Board constituted for the purposes of this section, for the Technical`
  line `Member referred to in sub-section (2) of section 84 of the Trade Marks Act, 1999, the Technical Member`
  line `shall be appointed under this Act and he shall be deemed to be the Technical Member for constituting the`
  line `Bench under the said sub-section (2) of section 84 for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (3693)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Penalty for infringement of layout-design.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3693&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes knowingly and`
  line `wilfully any of the provisions of section 18 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years, or with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend`
  line `to ten lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (3694)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Penalty for falsely representing a layout-design as registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3694&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall make any`
  line `representation with respect to a layout-design not being a registered layout-design, to the effect that it is a`
  line `registered layout-design.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to fifty`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, the use in India in relation to a layout-design of the word`
  line `"registered", or of any other expression referring whether expressly or impliedly to registration, shall be`
  line `deemed to import a reference to registration in the register, except--`
  line
  line `(a) where that word or other expression, is used in direct association with other words delineated`
  line `in characters at least as large as those in which that word or other expression is delineated and`
  line `indicating that the reference is to registration as a layout-design under the law of a country outside`
  line `India being a country under the law of which the registration referred to is in fact in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) where that other expression is of itself such as to indicate that the reference is to such`
  line `registration as is mentioned in clause (a); or`
  line
  line `(c) where that word is used in relation to a layout-design registered as a layout-design under the`
  line `law of a country outside India and in relation solely to such layout-design.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (3695)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Penalty for improperly describing a place of business as connected with the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3695&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `If any person uses on his place of business, or on any`
  line `document issued by him, or otherwise, words which would reasonably lead to the belief that his place of`
  line `business is, or is officially connected with, the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (3696)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Penalty for falsification of entries in the register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3696&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `If any person makes, or causes to be made,`
  line `a false entry in the register, or a writing falsely purporting to be a copy of an entry in the register, or`
  line `produces or tenders, or causes to be produced or tendered, in evidence any such writing, knowing the`
  line `entry or writing to be false, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (3697)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Forfeiture of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3697&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person is convicted of an offence under section 56, the court`
  line `convicting him may direct the forfeiture to Government of all goods and things by means of, or in relation`
  line `to, which the offence has been committed.`
  line
  line `(2) When a forfeiture is directed on a conviction and an appeal lies against the conviction, an appeal`
  line `shall lie against the forfeiture also.`
  line
  line `(3) When a forfeiture is directed on a conviction, the court, before whom the person is convicted, may`
  line `order any forfeited articles to be destroyed or otherwise disposed of as the court thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (3698)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Exemption of certain persons employed in ordinary course of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3698&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Where a person`
  line `accused of an offence under section 56 proves--`
  line
  line `(a) that in the case which is the subject of the charge he was so employed that it relates to the`
  line `duty of his employment, and was not interested in the profit accruing from such commission of`
  line `offence except the duty of his employment; and`
  line
  line `(b) that, having taken all reasonable precautions against committing the offence charged, he had,`
  line `at the time of commission of the alleged offence, no reason to suspect the genuineness of the`
  line `registered layout-design or a semiconductor integrated circuit in which such layout-design is`
  line `incorporated; and`
  line
  line `(c) that, on demand made by or on behalf of the prosecutor, he gave all the information in his`
  line `power with respect to the commission of such offence,`
  line
  line `he shall be acquitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (3699)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Procedure where invalidity of registration is pleaded by the accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3699&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the offence`
  line `charged under section 56 is in relation to a registered layout-design and the accused pleads that the`
  line `registration of the layout-design is invalid, the following procedure shall be followed:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the court is satisfied that such defence is prima facie tenable, it shall not proceed with the`
  line `charge but shall adjourn the proceeding for three months from the date on which the plea of accused`
  line `is recorded to enable the accused to file an application before the Appellate Board under this Act, for`
  line `the rectification of the register on the ground that the registration is invalid;`
  line
  line `(b) if the accused proves to the court that he has made such application within the time so limited`
  line `or within such further time as the time court may for sufficient cause may allow, the further`
  line `proceedings in the prosecution shall stand stayed till the disposal of such application for rectification;`
  line
  line `(c) if within a period of three months or within such extended time as may be allowed by the`
  line `court the accused fails to apply to the Appellate Board for rectification of the register, the court shall`
  line `proceed with the case as if the registration were valid .`
  line
  line `(2) Where before the institution of a complaint of an offence referred to in sub-section (1), any`
  line `application for the rectification of the register concerning the layout-design in question on the ground of`
  line `invalidity of the registration thereof has already been properly made to and is pending before the Appellate Board or the Registrar, the Court shall stay the further proceedings in the prosecution pending`
  line `the disposal of the application aforesaid and shall determine the charge against the accused in conformity`
  line `with the result of the application for rectification in so far as the complainant relies upon the registration`
  line `of his layout-design.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (3700)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3700&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Act is a company,`
  line `the company as well as every person in charge of, and responsible to, the company for the conduct of its`
  line `business at the time of the commission of the offence shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall`
  line `be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or that the commission of the offence is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association or individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (3701)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Cognizance of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3701&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance--`
  line
  line `(a) of an offence under section 56 or section 57 except on the complaint in writing made by the`
  line `registered proprietor or the registered user of a layout-design in respect of which the offence has been`
  line committed;
  line
  line `(b) of an offence under section 58 or section 59 except on complaint in writing made by the`
  line `Registrar or any officer authorised by him in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (3702)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Costs of defence or prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3702&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `In any prosecution under this Act, the court may order such`
  line `costs to be paid by the accused to the complainant, or by the complainant to the accused, as the court`
  line `deemed reasonable having regard to all the circumstances of the case and the conduct of the parties. Costs`
  line `so awarded shall be recoverable as if they were a fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (3703)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Information as to commission of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3703&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `An officer of the Government whose duty it is to`
  line `take part in the enforcement of the provisions of this Chapter, shall not be compelled in any court to say`
  line `when he got any information as to the commission of any offence against this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (3704)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Punishment of abetment in India of acts done out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3704&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `If any person, being within India,`
  line `abets the commission, without India, of any act which, if committed in India, would, under this Act, be an`
  line `offence, he may be tried for such abetment in any place in India in which he may be found, and be`
  line `punished therefor with the punishment to which he would be liable if he had himself committed in that`
  line `place the act which he abetted.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (3705)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Protection of security of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3705&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Registrar`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(a) not disclose any information relating to the registration of a layout-design or any application`
  line `relating to the registration of a layout-design under this Act which the Central Government considers`
  line `prejudicial to the interest of the security of India; and`
  line
  line `(b) take any action, including the cancellation of registration of a layout-design registered under`
  line `this Act, which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in the`
  line `interest of security of India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "interest of the security of India"`
  line `means any action necessary for the security of India which relates to the use of a layout-design or a`
  line `semiconductor integrated circuit incorporating a layout-design or an article incorporating such`
  line `semiconductor integrated circuit and which"`
  line
  line `(a) relates to fissionable materials or the materials from which they are derived; or`
  line
  line `(b) relates to the traffic in arms, ammunition and implements of war and to such traffic in other`
  line `goods and materials as is carried on directly or indirectly for the purpose of supplying a military`
  line `establishment; or`
  line
  line `(c) is taken in time of war or other emergency in international relations.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (3706)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3706&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against`
  line `any person in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (3707)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Certain persons to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3707&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Every person appointed, under this Act and every`
  line `Member of the Appellate Board shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (3708)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Implied warranty on sale of layout-design, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3708&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Where a registered layout-design, or a`
  line `semiconductor integrated circuit in which a registered layout-design is incorporated, or an article`
  line `incorporating such a semiconductor integrated circuit is sold or has been contracted for sale, the seller`
  line `shall be deemed to warrant that the registration, of such layout-design or the layout-design so`
  line `incorporated is genuine within the meaning of this Act unless the contrary is expressed in writing signed`
  line `by or on behalf of the seller and delivered at the time of the sale or contract to sell of such layout-design,`
  line `or semiconductor integrated circuit or article, as the case may be, and accepted by the buyer.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (3709)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Powers of Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3709&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `In all proceedings under this Act before the Registrar,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Registrar shall have all the powers, of a civil court for the purposes of receiving evidence,`
  line `administering oaths, enforcing the attendance of witnesses, compelling the discovery and production`
  line `of documents and issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) the Registrar may, subject to any rules in this behalf, made under section 96 make such orders`
  line `as to costs as he considers reasonable, and any such order shall be executable as decree to a civil`
  line court;
  line
  line `(c) the Registrar may, on an application made in the prescribed manner, review his own decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (3710)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Exercise of discretionary power by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3710&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 76, the`
  line `Registrar shall not exercise any discretionary or other power vested in him by this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder adversely to a person applying for the exercise of the power without (if so required by that`
  line `person within the prescribed time) giving to the person an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (3711)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Evidence before Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3711&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act before the Registrar, evidence`
  line `shall be given by affidavit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar may, if he thinks fit, take oral evidence in lieu of, or in addition to, such`
  line `evidence by affidavit.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (3712)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Death of party to a proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3712&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `If a person who is a party to a proceeding under this Act (not`
  line `being a proceeding before the Appellate Board or a court) dies pending the proceeding, the Registrar may,`
  line `on request, and on proof to his satisfaction of the transmission of the interest of the deceased person,`
  line `substitute in the proceeding his successor in interest in his place, or, if the Registrar is of opinion that the`
  line `interest of the deceased person is sufficiently represented by the surviving parties, permit the proceeding`
  line `to continue without the substitution of his successor in interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (3713)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Extention of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3713&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Registrar is satisfied, on application made to him in the prescribed`
  line `manner and accompanied by the prescribed fee, that there is sufficient cause for extending the time for`
  line `doing any act (not being a time expressly provided in the Act), whether the time so specified has expired`
  line `or not, he may, subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose, extend the time and inform the`
  line `parties accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to require the Registrar to hear the parties, before`
  line `disposing of an application for extension of time and no appeal shall lie from any order of the Registrar`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (3714)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title Abandonment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3714&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Where, in the opinion of the Registrar, an applicant is in default in the`
  line `prosecution of an application filed under this Act, the Registrar may, by notice require the applicant to`
  line `remedy the default within a time specified and after giving him, if so desired, an opportunity of being`
  line `heard, treat the application as abandoned, unless the default is remedied within the time specified in the`
  line notice.
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (3715)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Preliminary advice by the Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3715&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may, on application made to him in the`
  line `prescribed manner by any person who proposes to apply for the registration of a layout-design, give`
  line `advice as to whether the layout-design appears to him prima facie to be original.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on an application for the registration of a layout-design as to which the Registrar has given`
  line `advice as aforesaid in the affirmative made within three months after the advice was given, the Registrar,`
  line `after further investigation or consideration, gives notice, to the applicant of objection on the ground that`
  line `the layout-design is not original, the applicant shall be entitled, on giving notice of withdrawal of the`
  line `application within the prescribed period, to have repaid to him any fee paid on the filing of the`
  line application.
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (3716)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Registered user to be impleaded in certain proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3716&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every proceeding under`
  line `Chapter VII or under section 42, every registered user of a layout-design, who is not himself an applicant`
  line `in respect of any proceeding under that Chapter or section shall be made a party to the proceeding.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, a registered user so made a party to the`
  line `proceeding shall not be liable for any costs unless he enters an appearance and takes part in the`
  line proceeding.
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (3717)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Evidence of entries in register, etc., and things done by the Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3717&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of any`
  line `entry in the register or of any document referred to in sub-section (1) of section 87 purporting to becertified by the Registrar and sealed with the seal of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design`
  line `Registry shall be admitted in evidence in all courts and in all proceedings without further proof or`
  line `production of the original.`
  line
  line `(2) A certificate purporting to be under the hand of the Registrar as to any entry, matter or thing that`
  line `he is authorised by this Act or the rules to make or do shall be prima facie evidence of the entry having`
  line `been made, and of the contents thereof, or of the matter or things having been done or not done.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (3718)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Registrar and other officers not compellable to produce register, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3718&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar or any`
  line `other officer of the Semiconductor Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry shall not, in any legal`
  line `proceedings to which he is not a party, be compellable to produce the register or any other document in`
  line `his custody, the contents of which can be proved by the production of a certified copy issued under this`
  line `Act or to appear as a witness to prove the matters therein recorded unless by order of the court made or`
  line `special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (3719)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Certificate of validity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3719&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `If in any legal proceeding for rectification of the register before the`
  line `Appellate Board a decision is on contest given in favour of the registered proprietor of the layout-design`
  line `on the issue as to the validity of the registration of the layout-design, the Appellate Board may grant a`
  line `certificate to that effect, and if such a certificate is granted, then, in any subsequent legal proceedings in`
  line `which the said validity comes into question, the said proprietor on obtaining a final order or judgment in`
  line `his favour affirming validity of the registration of the layout-design shall, unless the said final order or`
  line `judgment for sufficient reason directs otherwise, be entitled to his full cost, charges and expenses as`
  line `between legal practitioner and client.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (3720)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Address for service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3720&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `An address for service stated in an application or notice of opposition`
  line `shall, for the purposes of the application or notice of opposition, be deemed to be the address of the`
  line `applicant or opponent, as the case may be, and all documents in relation to the application or notice of`
  line `opposition may be served by leaving them at or sending them by post to the address for service of the`
  line `applicant or opponent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (3721)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title Agents.
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3721&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Where, by or under this Act, any act, other then the making of an affidavit, is required`
  line `to be done before the Registrar by any person, the act may, subject to the rules made in this behalf, be`
  line `done, instead of by that person himself, by a person duly authorised in the prescribed manner, who is--`
  line
  line `(a) a legal practitioner, or`
  line
  line `(b) a person registered in the prescribed manner as a layout-design agent, or`
  line
  line `(c) a person in the sole and regular employment of the principal.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (3722)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Layout-design registered by an agent or representative without authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3722&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `If an agent or a`
  line `representative of the proprietor of a registered layout-design, without authority uses or attempts to register`
  line `or registers the layout-design in his own name, the proprietor shall be entitled to oppose the registration`
  line `applied for or secure its cancellation or rectification of the register so as to bring him as the registered`
  line `proprietor of the said layout-design by assignment in his favour:`
  line
  line `Provided that such action shall be taken within three years of the registered proprietor of the layoutdesign`
  line `becoming aware of the conduct of the agent or representative.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (3723)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title Indexes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3723&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `There shall be kept under the direction and supervision of the Registrar--`
  line
  line `(a) an index of registered layout-designs,`
  line
  line `(b) an index of layout-designs in respect of which applications for registration are pending.`
  line `(c) an index of the names of the proprietors of registered layout-designs, and`
  line
  line `(d) an index of the names of registered users.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (3724)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Documents open to public inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3724&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 25,--`
  line
  line `(a) the register and any document upon which any entry in the register is based;`
  line
  line `(b) every notice of opposition to the registration of a layout-design application for rectification`
  line `before the Registrar, counter-statement thereto, and any affidavit or document filed by the parties in`
  line `any proceedings before the Registrar; and`
  line
  line `(c) the indexes mentioned in section 86 and such other documents as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify;`
  line
  line `shall, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, be open to public inspection at the Semiconductor`
  line `Integrated Circuits Layout-Design Registry.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person may, on an application to the Registrar and on payment of such fees as may be`
  line `prescribed, obtain a certified copy of any entry in the register or any document referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (3725)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Reports of Registrar to be placed before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3725&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause to`
  line `be placed before both Houses of Parliament once a year a report respecting the execution by or under the`
  line `Registrar of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (3726)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Fees and surcharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3726&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be paid in respect of applications and registration and other`
  line `matters under this Act such fees and surcharge as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a fee is payable in respect of the doing of an act by the Registrar, the Registrar shall not do`
  line `that act until the fee has been paid.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a fee is payable in respect of the filing of a document at the Semiconductor Integrated`
  line `Circuits Layout-Design Registry, the document shall be deemed not to have been filed at the Registry`
  line `until the fee has been paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (3727)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Savings in respect of Chapter IX.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3727&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Chapter IX shall be construed so as to render`
  line `liable to any prosecution or punishment any servant of a master resident in India who in good faith acts in`
  line `obedience to the instructions of such master, and, on demand made by or on behalf of prosecutor, has`
  line `given full information as to his master and as to the instructions which he has received from his master.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (3728)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Declaration as to ownership of layout-design not registerable under the Registration Act, 1908.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3728&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), no document`
  line `declaring or purporting to declare the ownership or title of a person to a layout-design other than a`
  line `registered layout-design shall be registered under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (3729)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Government to be bound.`
  content `The provisions of this Act shall be binding on the Government.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3729&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (3730)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Convention countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3730&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `With a view to the fulfilment of a treaty, convention or arrangement`
  line `with any country outside India which affords to citizens of India similar privileges as granted to its own`
  line `citizens, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify such country to be a`
  line `convention country for providing the citizens of such convention country the similar privileges as granted`
  line `to the citizens of India under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section "country" includes any group of countries or union of`
  line `countries or inter-governmental organisation and the expression "convention country" shall be construed`
  line accordingly.
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (3731)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Provision as to reciprocity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3731&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `Where any country specified by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf by notification in the Official Gazette under section 93 does not accord to citizens of India the`
  line `same rights in respect of registration and protection of layout-design as it accords to its own nationals, no`
  line `national of such country shall be entitled, either solely or jointly with any other person,--`
  line
  line `(a) to apply for the registration of, or be registered as the proprietor of, a layout-design;`
  line
  line `(b) to be registered as the assignee of the proprietor of a registered layout-design; or`
  line
  line `(c) to apply for registration or be registered as a registered user of a layout-design under`
  line `section 25.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (3732)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Power of Central Government to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3732&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving`
  line `effect to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be`
  line `necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of five years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (3733)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048&sectionId=3733&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_75_00001_200037_1517807324048
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the other matters relating to the registered layout-designs to be entered in the register under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of applying to the Registrar for registration under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of advertising the application under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of notifying the correction or amendment in application under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of making application, the fee to be paid and the manner of giving notice under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of sending counter statement under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of submitting evidence under sub-section (4) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(h) the form of issuing certificate under sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of giving notice under sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of making applications to register the title under sub-section (1) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of applying to Registrar under sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(l) the document to be prescribed under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of issuing notice under sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of applications under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(o) the manner of making applications under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of making applications under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(q) the manner of issuing notice under sub-section (2) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(r) the procedure of cancelling registration under sub-section (3) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(s) the manner of applying to the Appellate Board under sub-section (1) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(t) the manner of giving notice under sub-section (3) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner of serving notice under sub-section (4) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of making application under sub-section (1) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner of making application under sub-section (2) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(x) the salaries and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and other Members under sub-section (1) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(y) the procedure for investigation of misbehaviour or incapacity of the Chairperson,`
  line `Vice-Chairperson and other Members under sub-section (3) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(z) the salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the officers and other employees`
  line `of the Appellate Board under sub-section (2) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(za) the manner of general superintendence by the Chairperson under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 39;`
  line
  line `(zb) the form of application, the affidavit, documents and other evidence and fee payable in`
  line `respect of, filing of such application and other fees for the services or execution of process to be`
  line `accompanied therewith under sub-section (2) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(zc) the time limit for filing the opposition under sub-section (3) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(zd) the form of making application and the fee to be a accompanied therewith under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(ze) the manner of giving notice under sub-section (2) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(zf) the form of appeal, the manner of verification of such appeal and the fee to be accompanied`
  line `therewith under sub-section (3) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zg) any other matter to be prescribed under clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(zh) the form of application under sub-section (1) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(zi) the manner of making application under sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(zj) the period to be prescribed under the first proviso to sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(zk) the manner of giving notice and opportunity of hearing to the parties under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 51;`
  line
  line `(zl) the period to be prescribed under sub-section (1) of section 53;`
  line
  line `(zm) the form of petition and particulars to be contained therein under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 53;`
  line
  line `(zn) the manner of reviewing decisions by the registrar under clause (c) of section 72;`
  line
  line `(zo) the time to be prescribed under section 73;`
  line
  line `(zp) the manner of making application and the fee to be accompanied therewith under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 76;`
  line
  line `(zq) the manner of making application under sub-section (1) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(zr) the period of giving notice of withdrawal of application under sub-section (2) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(zs) the manner of authorising a person under section 84;`
  line
  line `(zt) the manner of registering a person as a layout-design agent under clause (b) of section 84;`
  line
  line `(zu) the conditions to be prescribed under sub-section (1) of section 87;`
  line
  line `(zv) the fee payable under sub-section (2) of section 87;`
  line
  line `(zw) the fees and the surcharge to be paid under sub-section (1) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(zx) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
